1) What is Linux?
Linux is an operating system (OS).
An operating system is the middleman between:
You (user)
Applications (Chrome, Docker, Jenkins, etc.)
Hardware (CPU, RAM, Disk, Network)

Linux is:
Open-source (anyone can see & modify code)
Free (most of the time)
Very stable and secure
Used mostly on servers, cloud, DevOps, containers

üëâ Linux is not a single OS, it is a kernel.
Different companies add tools and create Linux distributions:
Ubuntu
CentOS
RHEL
Amazon Linux
**Linux is an open-source operating system kernel used to build secure, stable, multi-user operating systems mainly for servers and cloud environments.

2)Difference between Unix and Linux?
| Unix                | Linux               |
| ------------------- | ------------------- |
| Proprietary         | Open-source         |
| Paid                | Mostly Free         |
| Company owned       | Community driven    |
| Used in old systems | Used everywhere now |

Linux is an open-source Unix-like operating system, whereas Unix is proprietary and vendor-controlled.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Difference between Linux vs Windows vs macOS?
| Feature       | Linux          | Windows      | macOS         |
| ------------- | -------------- | ------------ | ------------- |
| Source        | Open           | Closed       | Closed        |
| Cost          | Free           | Paid         | Paid          |
| Usage         | Servers, Cloud | Personal PCs | Apple devices |
| Security      | Very High      | Medium       | High          |
| Customization | Very High      | Low          | Medium        |
| DevOps        | Best           | Poor         | Medium        |

Linux is preferred for servers due to security and flexibility, Windows is user-friendly for desktops, and macOS is Unix-based optimized for Apple hardware.

